                <head>No. 551.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 14, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 89.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    219, of the 19th ultimo, relative to the tariff between the United States and
                    Turkey, and to approve your protest to the Government of the Porte upon the
                    subject.</p>
                <p>Our treaty of 1862 must be adhered to, subject to the question as to the date
                    when the denunciation becomes effective under the treaty itself, as considered
                    in a late instruction addressed to you, and the negotiation for a new tariff
                    proposed by the Porte cannot prejudice the validity of your protest or affect
                    our rights thereunder.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
